=From the following form structure and its description:

HTML: {{ $json.html }}

Form description: {{ $json.description }}

Analyze the form and generate ONLY a valid JSON object with this structure:

{ "formSchema": { ... }, "uiSchema": { ... } }

Guidelines:

"formSchema" must be a valid JSON Schema Draft-07 object.

"uiSchema" must be a valid RJSF UI Schema using proper layout structures (e.g., VerticalLayout, Group, Control).

Use the correct "scope" format for RJSF: #/properties/fieldName.

Infer field types and formats from input elements and descriptions (e.g., type="date" â†’ format: "date", type="email" â†’ format: "email").

If a field involves file upload or attachment, use format: "data-url" and add "ui:widget": "file" in its controlâ€™s options.

Group logically related fields using Group elements with appropriate labels if the form has sections.

All required fields mentioned in the description must appear in the "required" array of formSchema.

The root of uiSchema must be a single VerticalLayout element wrapping all groups and controls.

Ensure the JSON output is compatible with RJSF Material Renderers and Material Cells.

Return ONLY the raw JSON object with formSchema and uiSchema. Do not include markdown, code blocks, or extra explanations.
